1030 void MmwDemo_CfgUpdate(void *srcPtr, uint32_t offset, uint32_t size, int8_t subFrameNum)
1031 {
1032  /* if subFrameNum undefined, broadcast to all sub-frames */
1033  if(subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
1034  {
1035  uint8_t indx;
1036  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
1037  {
1038  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx] + offset), srcPtr, size);
1039  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx], offset);
1040  }
1041  }
1042  else
1043  {
1044  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case
1045  where there is no advanced frame config) */
1046  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum] + offset), srcPtr, size);
1047  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum], offset);
1048  }
1049 }

1094 static void MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput

1099 )
1100 {
1101  MmwDemo_output_message_header header;
1102  MmwDemo_GuiMonSel *pGuiMonSel;
1103  MmwDemo_SubFrameCfg *subFrameCfg;
1104  uint32_t tlvIdx = 0;
1105  uint32_t index;
1106  uint32_t numPaddingBytes;
1107  uint32_t packetLen;
1108  uint8_t padding[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN];
1109  MmwDemo_output_message_tl tl[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_MAX];
1110  int32_t errCode;
1111  uint16_t *detMatrix = (uint16_t *)result->detMatrix.data;
1112  DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *objOut;
1113  cmplx16ImRe_t *azimuthStaticHeatMap;
1114  DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *objOutSideInfo;

1118  subFrameCfg = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[result->subFrameIdx];
1119 
1120  /* Get Gui Monitor configuration */
1121  pGuiMonSel = &subFrameCfg->guiMonSel;
1122 
1123  /* Clear message header */
1124  memset((void *)&header, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header));
1125 
1126  /******************************************************************
1127  Send out data that is enabled, Since processing results are from DSP,
1128  address translation is needed for buffer pointers
1129  *******************************************************************/
1130  {
1131  detMatrix = (uint16_t *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)detMatrix,
1132  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1133  &errCode);
1134  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)detMatrix!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1135 
1136  objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOut,
1137  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1138  &errCode);
1139  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOut != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1140 
1141  objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOutSideInfo,
1142  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1143  &errCode);
1144  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOutSideInfo != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1145 
1146  stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->stats,
1147  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1148  &errCode);
1149  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)stats != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1150 
1151 
1152  result->radarCube.data = (void *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data,
1153  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1154  &errCode);
1155  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1156  }
1157 
1158  /* Header: */
1159  header.platform = 0xA1642;
1160  header.magicWord[0] = 0x0102;
1161  header.magicWord[1] = 0x0304;
1162  header.magicWord[2] = 0x0506;
1163  header.magicWord[3] = 0x0708;
1164  header.numDetectedObj = result->numObjOut;
1165  header.version = MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD |
1166  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX << 8) |
1167  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR << 16) |
1168  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR << 24);
1169 
1170  packetLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header);
1171  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) || (pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 2) &&
1172  (result->numObjOut > 0))
1173  {
1174  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS;
1175  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
1176  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1177  tlvIdx++;
1178  }
1179  /* Side info */
1180  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) && (result->numObjOut > 0))
1181  {
1182  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS_SIDE_INFO;
1183  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
1184  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1185  tlvIdx++;
1186  }
1187  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange)
1188  {
1189  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_PROFILE;
1190  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
1191  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1192  tlvIdx++;
1193  }
1194  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile)
1195  {
1196  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_NOISE_PROFILE;
1197  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
1198  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1199  tlvIdx++;
1200  }
1201  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap)
1202  {
1203  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_AZIMUT_STATIC_HEAT_MAP;
1204  tl[tlvIdx].length = result->azimuthStaticHeatMapSize * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
1205  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1206  tlvIdx++;
1207  }
1208  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap)
1209  {
1210  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_DOPPLER_HEAT_MAP;
1211  tl[tlvIdx].length = subFrameCfg->numRangeBins * subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t);
1212  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1213  tlvIdx++;
1214  }
1215  if (pGuiMonSel->statsInfo)
1216  {
1217  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_STATS;
1218  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
1219  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
1220  tlvIdx++;
1221  }
1222 
1223  header.numTLVs = tlvIdx;

1568 static uint16_t MmwDemo_convertCfarToLinear(uint16_t codedCfarVal, uint8_t numVirtualAntennas)
1569 {
1570  uint16_t linearVal;
1571  float dbVal, linVal;
1572 
1573  /* dbVal is a float value from 0-100dB. It needs to
1574  be converted to linear scale..
1575  First, recover float dbVal that was encoded in CLI. */
1576  dbVal = (float)(codedCfarVal / MMWDEMO_CFAR_THRESHOLD_ENCODING_FACTOR);
1577 
1578  /* Now convert it to linear value according to the following:
1579  linear_value = dB_value * (256 / 6) * (numVirtualAntennas / (2^ ceil(log2(numVirtualAntennas)))) .
1580  */
1581  linVal = dbVal * (256.0 / 6.0) * ((float)numVirtualAntennas / (float)(1 << mathUtils_ceilLog2(numVirtualAntennas)));
1582 
1583  linearVal = (uint16_t) linVal;
1584  return (linearVal);
1585 }

1770  * be reconfigured every sub-frame). This cannot be alternatively done by calling

1772  * a utility API that computes the rxChanOffset that is part of ADC dataProperty

1799  * less than 16 (the minimal numDopplerBins supported in doppler DPU DSP).

2015 static int32_t MmwDemo_eventCallbackFxn(uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)
2016 {

2028  {
2029  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);

2034  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);

2036  }

2073  DebugP_log0("App: BSS stop (frame end) received\n");

2077  }

2083  }

2101  break;
2102  }
2103  }
2104  break;
2105  }
2106  default:
2107  {
2108  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
2109  break;
2110  }
2111  }
2112  return 0;
2113 }

2785  *****************************************************************/

2800  &nextSubFrameCfg->adcBufCfg,
2801  &dummyRxChanOffset[0]);

2803  {

3156  * if h/w and s/w both enabled, then s/w would leave h/w activated when it is done
3157  * so need to deactivate
3158  * (only s/w enabled cannot be the case here because we are checking for non-null h/w session)
3159  * Multi sub-frame case:
3160  * Given stop, we must have re-configured the next sub-frame by now which is next of the
3161  * last sub-frame i.e we must have re-configured sub-frame 0. So if sub-frame 0 had
3162  * h/w enabled, then it is left in active state and need to deactivate. For all
3163  * other cases, h/w was already deactivated when done.
3164  */
3165  if ((gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames == 1) ||
3166  ((gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames > 1) &&
3167  (gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[0].lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt != MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED))
3168  )
3169  {
3170  if (CBUFF_deactivateSession(gMmwMssMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
3171  {
3172  System_printf("CBUFF_deactivateSession failed with errorCode = %d\n", errCode);
3173  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
3174  }
3175  }
3176  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteHwSession();
3177  }
3178 
3179  /* Delete s/w session if it exists. S/w session never needs to be deactivated in stop because
3180  * it always (unconditionally) deactivates itself upon completion.
3181  */
3182  if(gMmwMssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle != NULL)
3183  {
3184  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteSwSession();
3185  }
3186 
3187  /* Print epilog */
3188  MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog();
3189 
3190  /* The sensor has been stopped successfully. Switch off the LED */
3191  GPIO_write (gMmwMssMCB.cfg.platformCfg.SensorStatusGPIO, 0U);
3192 
3193  gMmwMssMCB.sensorStopCount++;
3194 
3195  /* print for user */
3196  System_printf("Sensor has been stopped: startCount: %d stopCount %d\n",
3197  gMmwMssMCB.sensorStartCount,gMmwMssMCB.sensorStopCount);
3198 }
